*CORIA-CIFED Conferences - Joint Call for papers*
*Topics : Information Retrieval , Handwritting and Document analysis,
***

March 18th - 20th , 2010, Sousse,
http://sdnri2010.loria.fr <http://sdnri2010.loria.fr/>**

********************
Important Dates
******************* *
Abstract submission deadline: <deadline>November, 22nd</deadline>
Full paper submission deadline: <deadline>November, 29th</deadline>
Notification : January, 8th
Final date for camera-ready version : <deadline>January, 31st</deadline>

*******************
Description
****************** *
We are pleased to announce that CORIA2010 and CIFED2010, sponsored =

respectively by the ARIA (French Association for Information Research =

and Applications) and by the GRCE (Research Group for Handwritten and =

Document Analysis), will be held in Sousse, Tunisia during March 18-20, =

2010.

For the first time, this joint edition of CIFED and CORIA will be an =

outstanding occasion for researchers and practitioners at all levels of =

experience to share results/experience on common research topics in =

Information Research, Document Analysis, User & Interaction Models, =

Scalability, Performance Evaluation, etc., while keeping the own topics =

of the both communities (see the lists of topics of each conference below).

***************
CORIA Topics
***************
CORIA welcomes contributions related to any aspect of IR, including but =

not limited to:

=B7 IR Theory and Formal Models
=B7 Performance, Scalability, Architectures, Efficiency, Platforms
=B7 Text Categorization, Clustering
=B7 Cross-language retrieval, Multilingual retrieval, Machine translation =

for IR
=B7 Question answering, Natural language processing for IR, Summarization, =

Lexical acquisition
=B7 Information Extraction for IR, Text Mining
=B7 Multimedia IR, video retrieval, audio and music retrieval, cross-media =

retrieval,
. Image processing for IR, audio processing for IR
=B7 Web IR (e.g. link analysis, query log analysis, ad targeting)
=B7 Social network: blog and online-community search, opinion & sentiment =

detection
=B7 Collaborative filtering, recommender systems
=B7 Interactive IR, User studies, User models, Task-based IR, User =

interfaces and visualization
=B7 Knowledge engineering : Metadata, ontology, semantic Web
=B7 Digital Libraries, enterprise search, intranet search, desktop search
=B7 Domain-specific IR: genomic IR, geographic IR, legal IR, etc.
=B7 Distributed IR, peer to peer IR, Mobile IR, Fusion/Combination
=B7 Tools for IR: evaluation and test frameworks, platforms for =

experimentating systems
=B7 Query languages


*************
CIFED Topics
*************
The topics of interest of CIFED 2010 include, but are not limited to:

=B7 Basic research and methodologies for document and handwriting processing
=B7 Pattern recognition and image processing techniques
=B7 Acquisition, compression, segmentation of document image and handwriting
=B7 Document retrieval and understanding Systems (CBIR, spotting, =85)
=B7 Features extraction and organization for indexation purposes
=B7 Frameworks and strategies for document analysis
=B7 Layout analysis, automatic recognition and CMS
=B7 Character and handwriting recognition
=B7 Graphics and maps recognition
=B7 Writers and Signatures identification
=B7 Camera-based document processing and mobile devices, =85
=B7 Document databases and digital libraries and scalability
=B7 Multimedia Documents (videos, web, =85)
=B7 Sketching Interfaces
=B7 Performance Evaluation
=B7 Applications

******************
Submission
******************
Manuscripts of maximum 14 pages are encouraged to be submitted. Papers =

must describe original work on any of the related topics. The format =

templates and instructions for paper submission will be available in the =

Conference web site. The deadline for paper submission is <deadline>November 29, =

2009</deadline>. Languages for papers can be French or English.
Best papers will be published in a special issue of Document Num=E9rique =

Journal.

CORIA: http://coria2010.loria.fr
CIFED: http://cifed2010.loria.fr

Program Committee Chairs:
Brigitte GRAU (CORIA)
Jean-Yves RAMEL (CIFED)

